dct_description_sm: Prepared by the Army Map Service (GE), Corps of Engineers, U. S. Army, Washington D.C. , original map compiled by US Geological Survey. Variant title: Indiana 1:25,000. Filing title: Cedar Grove, Indiana. Standard map series designation: Series V851 Sheet 4062 IV SW. Edition 1--AMS. Transverse Mercator projection. Army Map Service , V851. Relief shown by contours and spot heights. Shows roads, railroads, boundaries, buildings, mines, and natural features. Marginal maps: Index to boundaries -- Index to adjoining sheets. Contour interval 10 feet. "Copied in 1957 from Indiana, 1:24,000, USGS, Cedar Grove, 1955. Original map compiled by photogrammetric methods by U.S. Geological Survey from aerial photographs taken 1954. Horizontal and vertical control by USGS and USC&GS and Indiana Flood Control and Water Resources Commission. ... Map field checked, 1955. Scale changed, Universal Transverse Mercator Grid added, marginal data revised, 1957." "First Printing, 1-58." "Printed by Army Map Service, Corps of Engineers, 1-58." Printed with vegetation.
Imprint: Washington, D.C. : Army Map Service, Corps of Engineers, 1958.
Dimensions: maps 56 x 45 cm or smaller
dct_creator_sm: Geological Survey (U.S.); United States. Army Map Service
